gpgme
-------------------------------------------
GPGME  (GnuPG Made Easy) is a C language library that allows to add 
support for cryptography to a program. It is designed to make access to 
public key crypto engines like GnuPG easier for applications. 
GPGME provides a high-level crypto API for encryption, decryption, 
signing, signature verification and key management.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.21-2
  gnupg-1.4.5-1
  libgpg-error-1.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.21-2
  autoconf2.5-2.60-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-1
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.2.6-1
  gawk-3.1.5-2
  gcc-core-3.4.4-1
  libtool1.5-1.5.23a-1
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://www.gnupg.org/(en)/related_software/gpgme/

Canonical download:
  ftp://ftp.gnupg.org/gcrypt/gpgme/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack gpgme-1.0.3-1-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./gpgme-1.0.3-1.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gpgme-1.0.3-1-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/gpgme-1.0.3-1.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgpgme-devel-1.0.3-1.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgpgme11-1.0.3-1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary packages:

(gpgme)
  /etc/postinstall/gpgme.sh
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/gpgme-1.1.2.README
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.1.2/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/gpgme-1.1.2/COPYING
